In this article, President Biden addresses the recent massacre at an elementary school in Uvalde, Texas. He expresses his sorrow and frustration at the recurring incidents of gun violence in the country, particularly in schools. The President calls on the nation to stand up to the gun lobby and take action to prevent further tragedies. He highlights the need for commonsense gun laws and points out that such laws have had a positive impact in the past. The President questions the necessity of assault weapons and criticizes the aggressive marketing tactics of gun manufacturers. He emphasizes that most Americans support commonsense gun laws and urges elected officials to take action. The President also reflects on the rarity of mass shootings in other countries and calls for courage and determination to address the issue. He concludes by expressing his prayers for the families affected by the tragedy and emphasizes the need for support and action in the face of such devastating events.